						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">King: Rājarāja III Year 14: 1240 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Records a gift of ninety sheep by a shepherd <hi rend="italic">(iḍaiyan)</hi> Vīraṭṭan Koṅgan for burning a perpetual lamp to the god, Āḷuḍaiyār Tiruvālīśvara-uḍaiya Mahādēvar of Kāṭṭūr <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Rājēndrachōḷanallūr at Perumbēḍu in Puliyūr-kōṭṭam, (a sub-division) of Jayaṅgoṇḍachōḷa-maṇḍalam. It is also mentioned that a shepherd Śiṟṟēri Seṭṭi (a resident) of Tiruvāḷvāyil received the gift and agreed to supply (oil). </p>						

						</summary>
